                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>Kathleen Wilkinson Wootten collection, 1909-1966.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>The Kathleen Wilkinson Wootten Collection contains her personal and professional correspondence, greeting cards, journals, maps, materials relating to the Health and P.E. Department at Georgia State College for Women where she taught health from 1917-1952. The collection also contains numerous articles on various health subjects such as sex education. Finally, there are also miscellaneous papers such as Wootten's business correspondence and resumes. The collection covers most of her life beginning in 1909 and ending in 1966. However, there are gaps in each decade, notably in the 1920s and 1930s. </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>Georgia College & State University</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>

                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/cre">Creator</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>James Calvin Bonner papers, 1811-1984.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>The personal papers of James C. Bonner contain 25.5 cubic feet of eight series of forty-four file boxes, plus two individual oversized boxes containing maps, posters, and Confederate and German currency. The materials span the years from 1811-1984, with the most concentration in the years 1930-1973. Contents include published and unpublished manuscripts written by Dr. Bonner, drafts of his journal articles, course notes and syllabi, photographs, scrapbooks, genealogical material, awards, nineteenth-century letters, Civil War materials, and newspaper clippings of events in areas of professional and personal interest. </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>Georgia College & State University</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>
